# Styling & UI Rules

## Tailwind CSS v4 Configuration

- Tailwind is configured via **CSS** in `app/globals.css` and PostCSS — there is **no `tailwind.config.js`**.
- Design tokens are CSS custom properties in `:root` / `.dark` using **oklch** color space.
- Tokens are mapped to Tailwind via `@theme inline` in `globals.css`.
- To add new design tokens, add them to `globals.css` under `:root` and `.dark`, then map them in `@theme inline`.

## Design Token Usage

Always use semantic token classes — never hard-code colors:

```tsx
// GOOD — uses design tokens
<div className="bg-background text-foreground border-border" />
<button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground" />
<span className="text-muted-foreground" />
<div className="bg-accent text-accent-foreground" />

// BAD — hard-coded colors
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900" />
<div className="bg-[#1E3A5F]" />
```

## Styling Rules

- **No inline styles** unless trivial (e.g., dynamic `style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-barlow)' }}`).
- Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling.
- Use the `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'

<div className={cn(
  'px-4 py-2 rounded-md',
  isActive && 'bg-accent/10 text-accent',
  !isActive && 'text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground',
)} />
```

- Never mix logic and presentation — keep className computation clean.
- Use consistent spacing: follow the project's existing spacing scale (`gap-2`, `p-4`, `p-8`, etc.).

## shadcn/ui Components

- **Never edit files in `components/ui/` manually.** They are managed by the shadcn CLI.
- To add a new primitive: `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
- Import from `@/components/ui/<component>`:

```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '@/components/ui/card'
import { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge'
```

- Use shadcn variants and sizes — do not override with custom classes unless extending.
- Style: `new-york`. Icon library: `lucide-react`.

## Component Composition

- Build domain components by **composing** shadcn primitives — not by copying/modifying them.
- Domain components go in `components/customer/` or `components/admin/`.
- Every reusable UI element must be a proper component — no duplicated JSX blocks.

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: base classes for mobile, then `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` for breakpoints.
- Use `hidden md:flex` / `md:hidden` patterns for responsive visibility (see `CustomerNavbar`).
- Test layouts at all breakpoints.

## Icons

- Use `lucide-react` exclusively. Import individual icons:

```tsx
import { ShoppingCart, User, Search } from 'lucide-react'
```

- Standard sizing: `className="w-4 h-4"` (small), `className="w-5 h-5"` (medium).

## Typography

- Body text: Inter (`font-sans`).
- Display / headings: Barlow (`font-display` or `style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-barlow)' }}`).
- Use Tailwind typography utilities: `text-sm`, `text-lg`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `tracking-tight`.

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must have `aria-label` when visible text is absent.
- Use semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<header>`, `<section>`, `<button>`.
- Toggle buttons must set `aria-expanded`.
- Form inputs must have associated `<label>` elements.
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA against the oklch token values.
